---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CrystalMark from '../components/CrystalMark.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Build Crystal"
  description="Build Crystal is a small shop building AI workers that actually work. Run by Austin VanAlstyne. We use our own product."
  active="about"
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="frame">
      <p class="eyebrow">About Build Crystal</p>
      <h1>Tired of AI pitches that don't survive the real world?</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Same. We build workers &mdash; not platforms, not copilots, not dashboards. You hire one,
        we build it, we run it. One role at a time. Day one is rough. Day 30 it's genius.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/#roles" class="btn btn-primary">See who's available</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-secondary" data-hire data-role="general">Book a working session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY -->
  <section class="band band-paper">
    <div class="frame">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="col-head">
          <p class="eyebrow-sm">Why this exists</p>
          <h2>Hiring is broken. AI keeps pretending the answer is a dashboard.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-body">
          <p>
            Small businesses lose weeks to hiring. Post the job. Screen forty resumes. Phone-screen the
            ones that can write a sentence. Interview the short list. Pick one. Train them for three
            months. Then watch half of them leave inside a year. Every week the seat sits open is a week
            of missed calls and overworked staff covering for it.
          </p>
          <p>
            Meanwhile, every AI company wants to sell you a platform to configure yourself. Prompt
            templates. Workflow builders. "Just wire it up." That's not help. That's homework.
          </p>
          <p class="kicker">We wanted to sell help, not homework.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BIG PULL QUOTE -->
  <section class="pull-band">
    <div class="frame pull-frame">
      <span class="pull-mark" aria-hidden="true"><CrystalMark size={28} /></span>
      <blockquote>
        Day one is rough. Day 30 it's genius. Every correction sticks, every night it reviews what it
        learned, and it shows up the next morning a little better than it was.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="pull-attrib">Austin VanAlstyne &middot; Build Crystal</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WE TAKE OUR OWN MEDICINE -->
  <section class="band band-paper">
    <div class="frame">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="col-head">
          <p class="eyebrow-sm">How we run Build Crystal</p>
          <h2>We take our own medicine.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-body">
          <p>
            Build Crystal runs with one human employee &mdash; Austin &mdash; and a team of AI workers.
            The same workers we hire out to customers.
          </p>
          <p>
            The receptionist that picks up when you call is one of ours. The L1 desk answering
            support tickets from our own customers is one of ours. Scheduling, intake, the boring
            paperwork in between &mdash; same shop, same workers. When we ship a new role, it lives
            inside Build Crystal before it goes anywhere near your business.
          </p>
          <p>
            If the receptionist drops a call, we lose the customer &mdash; not you. If the L1
            confidently answers wrong, we eat the ticket &mdash; not you. We pay the cost of our
            own mistakes first.
          </p>
          <div class="inline-callout">
            If you want to know whether it works, you're already in the demo. Pick up the phone.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT'S LIVE -->
  <section class="band band-ink">
    <div class="frame">
      <p class="eyebrow-sm on-dark">What's shipping, right now</p>
      <h2 class="on-dark">Two workers live, three more in training.</h2>
      <div class="live-grid">
        <div class="live-card">
          <div class="live-top">
            <span class="live-tag live">Live</span>
            <span class="live-where">Inside Build Crystal</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Receptionist</h3>
          <p>
            Answers calls, books and reschedules, takes messages, routes judgment calls. In use as the
            front desk for Build Crystal. Available for customer deployments.
          </p>
          <a href="/workers/receptionist" class="live-link">Role detail &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="live-card">
          <div class="live-top">
            <span class="live-tag live">Live</span>
            <span class="live-where">Crystal customer support</span>
          </div>
          <h3>L1 Help Desk</h3>
          <p>
            Works the ticket queue overnight and weekends &mdash; password resets, access requests,
            common L1 work. Running our own customer support desk inside Build Crystal. Available
            for customer deployments.
          </p>
          <a href="/workers/l1-helpdesk" class="live-link">Role detail &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="live-card pending">
          <div class="live-top">
            <span class="live-tag pending">In training</span>
            <span class="live-where">Next three</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Intake, bookkeeper, scheduler</h3>
          <p>
            Three more roles getting trained up right now. Getting in early lets you shape what the
            worker does from day one. Tell us the seat you're trying to fill and we'll tell you if
            it's on the next cut.
          </p>
          <a href="#contact" class="live-link" data-hire data-role="other">Tell us about your seat &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW A SESSION GOES -->
  <section class="band band-paper">
    <div class="frame">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="col-head">
          <p class="eyebrow-sm">How a working session actually goes</p>
          <h2>15 minutes. No pitch deck.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-body">
          <p>
            We don't do demos. We do working sessions. You tell us the seat you're trying to fill, the
            tools you use, the pay range, and what's been driving you crazy about the role.
          </p>
          <p>
            We tell you honestly whether we can cover it, how much it would run, and what the first 28
            days would look like. If we can't cover it, we say so. If we can cover it but you shouldn't
            buy it yet, we say that too. If we can cover it and you should, we set a start date for the
            pilot.
          </p>
          <p class="kicker">No slide deck. No "intro to AI." Just the seat and the math.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE WON'T DO -->
  <section class="band band-paper band-divider">
    <div class="frame">
      <p class="eyebrow-sm">Things we're not going to do</p>
      <h2>What we won't do.</h2>
      <ul class="wont-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Sell you a tool to configure yourself.</strong>
          <span>We're a managed service. If you want a prompt builder, Zapier has one.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pretend setup is a click.</strong>
          <span>Setup takes 3 to 5 days. We come out, we onboard the worker, we hang out while it ramps.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pretend day one is genius.</strong>
          <span>Day one is rough. Same as any new hire. That's the honest part.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Sell a multi-agent platform before one worker is proven.</strong>
          <span>One role. One worker. One customer at a time.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BIG CTA -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="frame cta-wrap">
      <div>
        <h2>Hiring for a role we cover?</h2>
        <p>Book a 15-minute working session. We'll tell you honestly whether we're a fit.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary big" data-hire data-role="general">Book a working session</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  /* HERO */
  .hero { padding: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 6rem) 0 clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.2vw, 3.8rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    max-width: 24ch;
  }
  .hero .lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.7vw, 1.25rem);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  /* Section shells */
  .band { padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .band-divider { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .band-paper { background: var(--paper); }
  .band-ink { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); border-top: 0; }

  .eyebrow-sm {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .eyebrow-sm.on-dark { color: #ffb383; }

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.25rem; }
  }
  .col-head h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.8vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    max-width: 18ch;
  }
  .col-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .col-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .col-body .kicker {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .inline-callout {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--accent-wash);
    border-radius: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* PULL BAND */
  .pull-band {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .pull-frame {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .pull-mark {
    display: inline-flex;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .pull-band blockquote {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.4vw, 1.9rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .pull-attrib {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  /* DARK BAND (What's live) */
  .band-ink h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.8vw, 2.1rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .band-ink h2.on-dark { color: var(--paper); }
  .live-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(16rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .live-card {
    background: #1d2028;
    border: 1px solid #2a2e37;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .live-card.pending { background: transparent; border-style: dashed; border-color: #3a3e48; }
  .live-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .live-tag {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.22rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }
  .live-tag.live { background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.18); color: #86efac; }
  .live-tag.pending { background: rgba(234, 90, 41, 0.22); color: #ffb383; }
  .live-where {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #9aa0ad;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .live-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .live-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #c7c9cf;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .live-link {
    margin-top: auto;
    color: #ffb383;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 120ms ease;
  }
  .live-link:hover { color: #ffd4b8; }

  /* WONT LIST */
  .band-paper.band-divider h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.8vw, 2rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .wont-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(20rem, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .wont-list li {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }
  .wont-list li strong {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .wont-list li span {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* CTA BAND */
  .cta-band { padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem) 0; background: var(--accent-wash); }
  .cta-wrap {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  .btn.big { padding: 1rem 1.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
</style>
